FT  17 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Marks and Spencer
Total payments to Sir Richard Greenbury, chairman and chief executive of
Marks and Spencer, increased from Pounds 708,551 to Pounds 806,626 last
year, according to the company's annual report.
Sir Richard's basic pay increased 11 per cent to Pounds 594,620, while his
performance-related bonus increased almost 25 per cent to Pounds 126,506.
Contributions to his pension increased from Pounds 73,876 to Pounds 85,500.
M&amp;S increased pre-tax profits by 25 per cent last year to Pounds 736.5m on
turnover up 3 per cent at Pounds 5.9bn.
